's keep an eye out for potential assertion errors using RestAssured's JsonPath syntax!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Finalizing path format and generics**\\n\\nI’ve figured out the path format as \\\"store.books[0].title,\\\" which seems good. Now, considering potential generics, I see that `expectBody(String, List<Argument>, Matcher<?>)` works with `equalTo(\\\"Effective Java\\\")`, returning a `Matcher<String>`. However, I need to remember not to compile or run tests right now as per instructions. Finally, I should mention concisely that no tests have been executed. That should keep everything clear!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added a dedicated test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/ResponseSpecificationImplInner_applyArguments_closure15Test.java`\n\nThe test exercises `ResponseSpecificationImpl.applyArguments` through the public `ResponseSpecBuilder.expectBody(String, List<Argument>, Matcher)` API using formatted JSON path arguments, then validates the resulting specification against a `ResponseBuilder` response.\n\nI did not run tests, per workflow instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a8042e9d52adfeb016a0151274cc081a3bebd41b06c149dc4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2386, "output": 619, "cacheRead": 72192, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 75197, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778471195649, "responseId": "resp_0a8042e9d52adfeb016a01511c772881a38aa5ec14fecbe2fd"}}
